    "body": "@3xtr4t3rr3str14l Normally our network detects new peer through `peer:connect` event from libp2p/discv5 and it'll do handshake (send/receive/compare status messages) in order to create a new peer. If a new peer does not have expected Status message, we'll disconnect that peer. I guess that's the end of Witti period and our bootstrap peers switched to Altona already, so we need to try again to reproduce the issue with Altona.\r\n\r\n> also, do you mean that we should have an option to suppress these messages via a keyboard combo or similar?\r\n\r\nI just mean we should be able to do `Ctrl + C` to stop the process, normally we can do that nicely.\r\n\r\nI'll post Altona configuration here so that you can sync Altona and see if the issue still happens.",
